19.03	Victor_Vancier	Victor Vancier	Victor Vancier (born December 25, 1956), commonly referred to by his Hebrew name, Chaim Ben Pesach (Hebrew: â€Ž) is an American political activist and the founder and director of the United States-based Kahanist organization, Jewish Task Force (JTF) and the former National Chairman of the Jewish Defense League (JDL) in the United States. In 1987, he was convicted on charges related to a series of bombings conducted in order to free Soviet Jews during his time with the JDL. He served over five years in federal prison for his involvement in 18 bombings in New York and Washington.	
